WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:25.573
Aah!

3
00:00:28.452 --> 00:00:29.600
Wee-be-be-bee.

4
00:00:29.716 --> 00:00:31.326
Will you take a look at that?

5
00:00:31.404 --> 00:00:32.859
Pretty pathetic. huh?

6
00:00:32.975 --> 00:00:34.317
Well. you'll never
believe this.

7
00:00:34.393 --> 00:00:35.584
but that llama
you're looking at

8
00:00:35.698 --> 00:00:37.310
was once a human being

9
00:00:37.424 --> 00:00:38.920
And not just
any human being

10
00:00:39.036 --> 00:00:40.301
That guy was an emperor

11
00:00:40.417 --> 00:00:42.335
A rich. powerful ball
of charisma

12
00:00:42.450 --> 00:00:43.371
Oh. yeah!

13
00:00:44.637 --> 00:00:45.862
This is his story

14
00:00:46.975 --> 00:00:48.701
Well. actually my story

15
00:00:48.816 --> 00:00:51.502
That's right--
I'm that llama

16
00:00:51.616 --> 00:00:53.725
The name is Kuzco

17
00:00:53.802 --> 00:00:56.029
Emperor Kuzco

18
00:00:56.143 --> 00:00:57.906
I was the world's
nicest guy.

19
00:00:58.021 --> 00:00:59.515
and they ruined my life
for no reason

20
00:00:59.631 --> 00:01:01.204
Oh. is that hard to believe?

21
00:01:01.281 --> 00:01:02.968
Look. I tell you what
You go back away--

22
00:01:03.045 --> 00:01:05.040
you know. before
I was a llama.

23
00:01:05.117 --> 00:01:06.421
and this will all make sense

24
00:01:06.536 --> 00:01:09.259
All right. now see.
that's a little too far back

25
00:01:09.335 --> 00:01:11.100
Oh. ho! Look at me!

26
00:01:11.215 --> 00:01:12.519
That's me as a baby

27
00:01:12.634 --> 00:01:14.359
Waah!

28
00:01:15.701 --> 00:01:17.811
Ahem! All right.
let's move ahead

29
00:01:34.956 --> 00:01:36.451
Oh. yeah.

30
00:01:36.566 --> 00:01:38.447
Theme song guy: There are
despots and dictators

31
00:01:38.563 --> 00:01:40.555
Political manipulators

32
00:01:40.671 --> 00:01:44.927
There are blue bloods
with the intellects of fleas

33
00:01:45.043 --> 00:01:47.000
There are kings
and catty tyrants

34
00:01:47.114 --> 00:01:49.837
Who are so lacking
in refinements

35
00:01:49.915 --> 00:01:51.870
They'd be better suited
swinging from the trees

36
00:01:53.519 --> 00:01:55.474
He was born and raised
to rule

37
00:01:55.590 --> 00:01:57.737
No one has ever been
as cool

38
00:01:57.852 --> 00:02:00.769
In a thousand years
of aristocracy

39
00:02:02.302 --> 00:02:04.489
An enigma and a mystery

40
00:02:04.566 --> 00:02:06.598
In Mesoamerican history

41
00:02:06.713 --> 00:02:09.782
The quintessence of
perfection that is he

42
00:02:11.431 --> 00:02:12.695
Ok. this is the real me

43
00:02:12.811 --> 00:02:13.656
Not this

44
00:02:13.808 --> 00:02:14.921
- This
- Not this.

45
00:02:15.037 --> 00:02:16.418
- Winner!
- Loser.

46
00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:18.526
Ok. see this palace?

47
00:02:18.641 --> 00:02:20.021
Everyone in it
is at my command

48
00:02:20.098 --> 00:02:21.020
Check this out

49
00:02:22.055 --> 00:02:23.245
Butler.

50
00:02:23.360 --> 00:02:25.276
Chef.

51
00:02:25.353 --> 00:02:26.618
Theme song guy.

52
00:02:26.695 --> 00:02:28.039
Oh. yeah!

53
00:02:28.116 --> 00:02:30.338
He's the sovereign lord
of the nation

54
00:02:30.455 --> 00:02:32.717
He's the hippest cat
in creation

55
00:02:32.831 --> 00:02:35.402
He's the alpha.
the omega. A to Z

56
00:02:36.860 --> 00:02:38.625
And this perfect world
will spin

57
00:02:38.740 --> 00:02:40.771
Around his every
little whim

58
00:02:40.848 --> 00:02:43.650
'Cause this perfect world
begins and ends with

59
00:02:43.764 --> 00:02:44.608
Me.

60
00:02:44.723 --> 00:02:45.681
What's his name?

61
00:02:45.796 --> 00:02:49.401
Kuzco

62
00:02:49.516 --> 00:02:50.591
That's his name

63
00:02:50.705 --> 00:02:52.240
Kuzco

64
00:02:52.354 --> 00:02:54.539
He's the king
of the world

65
00:02:54.616 --> 00:02:56.536
Kuzco

66
00:02:56.651 --> 00:02:58.223
Is he hip or what?

67
00:02:58.300 --> 00:03:00.063
Kuzco

68
00:03:00.139 --> 00:03:01.674
Yeah

69
00:03:03.401 --> 00:03:05.164
Gow!

70
00:03:05.318 --> 00:03:06.890
You threw off my groove!

71
00:03:07.006 --> 00:03:08.848
I'm sorry.
but you've thrown off

72
00:03:08.925 --> 00:03:11.110
the emperor's groove.

73
00:03:11.224 --> 00:03:12.990
Sorry!

74
00:03:13.067 --> 00:03:14.752
You were saying?

75
00:03:14.867 --> 00:03:21.121
What's his name?
Kuzco

76
00:03:21.274 --> 00:03:24.151
Kuzco

77
00:03:24.610 --> 00:03:26.681
That's his name

78
00:03:28.599 --> 00:03:30.824
Is he hip or what?

79
00:03:30.938 --> 00:03:35.080
Don't you know he's
the king of the world?

80
00:03:35.235 --> 00:03:39.415
Whoa. yeah

81
00:03:39.531 --> 00:03:40.644
Oww!

82
00:03:42.789 --> 00:03:43.671
Ha!

83
00:03:43.748 --> 00:03:44.632
Boom. baby!

84
00:03:44.861 --> 00:03:46.281
Aah! Your Highness.

85
00:03:46.358 --> 00:03:47.968
it is time for you
to choose your bride.

86
00:03:48.084 --> 00:03:49.388
Allrighty

87
00:03:49.463 --> 00:03:51.842
Trot out
the ladies

88
00:03:51.956 --> 00:03:52.878
Let's take a look-see.

89
00:03:52.955 --> 00:03:55.294
Hate your hair.
Not likely.

90
00:03:55.371 --> 00:03:57.365
Yikes. yikes. yikes.

91
00:03:57.441 --> 00:03:58.860
and let me guess.

92
00:03:58.937 --> 00:04:00.931
You have
a great personality.

93
00:04:01.046 --> 00:04:02.812
Is this really
the best you could do?

94
00:04:02.889 --> 00:04:05.074
Oh. yes. Oh. no.
I mean. perhaps--

95
00:04:05.189 --> 00:04:06.800
What
is he babbling about?

96
00:04:06.877 --> 00:04:09.139
He's like the thing
that wouldn't shut up

97
00:04:09.253 --> 00:04:12.860
Anyway. still wondering about
that llama in the opening?

98
00:04:13.896 --> 00:04:16.925
Well. let me show you the people
responsible for ruining my life

99
00:04:18.499 --> 00:04:20.915
First. there's Pacha

100
00:04:21.029 --> 00:04:21.872
Uh. excuse me.

101
00:04:21.987 --> 00:04:23.483
I'm here to see
Emperor Kuzco.

102
00:04:23.598 --> 00:04:25.095
You see.
I got this summons--

103
00:04:25.209 --> 00:04:26.860
Inside. up the stairs.
and to the left

104
00:04:26.975 --> 00:04:28.586
Just follow the signs

105
00:04:28.661 --> 00:04:31.461
Oh. great.
Thanks a lot.

106
00:04:31.538 --> 00:04:35.374
Uh. and don't be fooled
by the folksy peasant look

107
00:04:35.488 --> 00:04:36.869
Oh!

108
00:04:37.021 --> 00:04:38.826
Pardon me
That's mine

109
00:04:38.940 --> 00:04:39.822
Oh. here you go.

110
00:04:39.899 --> 00:04:41.242
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

111
00:04:42.315 --> 00:04:43.927
Aah! Oh. hey.
Are you all right?

112
00:04:44.004 --> 00:04:44.884
Here. Let me. uh--

113
00:04:44.961 --> 00:04:45.767
Oh. you're
so very kind.

114
00:04:45.882 --> 00:04:46.726
What happened?

115
00:04:46.843 --> 00:04:47.687
Well. I...

116
00:04:47.802 --> 00:04:49.678
I threw off
the emperor's groove.

117
00:04:49.755 --> 00:04:50.831
- What?
- His groove!

118
00:04:50.946 --> 00:04:52.288
The rhythm in which
he lives his life.

119
00:04:52.363 --> 00:04:53.552
his pattern of behavior.

120
00:04:53.668 --> 00:04:54.627
I threw it off.

121
00:04:54.742 --> 00:04:57.043
and the emperor had me
thrown out the window.

122
00:04:57.120 --> 00:04:59.153
Oh. really?

123
00:04:59.269 --> 00:05:00.305
I'm supposed
to see him today.

124
00:05:00.458 --> 00:05:01.608
Don't throw off
his groove!

125
00:05:01.723 --> 00:05:02.644
Oh. ok.

126
00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:04.331
Beware the groove.

127
00:05:04.446 --> 00:05:05.711
Hey. are you
gonna be all right?

128
00:05:05.826 --> 00:05:07.283
Groove.

129
00:05:07.399 --> 00:05:08.973
Kuzco: You see
what I mean?

130
00:05:09.088 --> 00:05:11.773
This guy's trouble.
but as bad as he is.

131
00:05:11.848 --> 00:05:13.880
he is nothing compared
to what's coming up next

132
00:05:14.302 --> 00:05:15.262
And why have you
come here today?

133
00:05:16.067 --> 00:05:16.949
Well

134
00:05:17.026 --> 00:05:19.903
Your Highness--
I mean. Your Grace.

135
00:05:19.980 --> 00:05:22.281
Ok. gang
Check out this piece of work

136
00:05:22.358 --> 00:05:25.235
This is Yzma.
the emperor's advisor--

137
00:05:25.350 --> 00:05:28.187
living proof that dinosaurs
once roamed the Earth

138
00:05:28.264 --> 00:05:30.565
And let's not forget
Yzma's right-hand man

139
00:05:30.641 --> 00:05:32.483
Every decade or so
she gets a new one

140
00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:34.209
This year's model
is called Kronk

141
00:05:36.550 --> 00:05:38.237
Yeah. I got
that there. Yzma.

142
00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:40.845
Unh!

143
00:05:40.959 --> 00:05:42.723
Yep. that's Kronk

144
00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:45.716
Now lately. Yzma's
gotten into this bad habit

145
00:05:45.831 --> 00:05:48.016
of trying to run the country
behind my back.

146
00:05:48.093 --> 00:05:50.012
and I’m thinkin'
that's got to stop

147
00:05:50.165 --> 00:05:52.081
It is no concern
of mine

148
00:05:52.197 --> 00:05:53.119
whether your family
has...

149
00:05:53.233 --> 00:05:54.230
What was it again?

150
00:05:54.345 --> 00:05:55.802
Um. food.

151
00:05:55.918 --> 00:05:57.951
Ha! You really should
have thought of that

152
00:05:58.065 --> 00:05:59.752
before you
became peasants.

153
00:05:59.867 --> 00:06:00.903
We're through here.

154
00:06:01.019 --> 00:06:02.860
Take him away. Next!

155
00:06:02.935 --> 00:06:04.509
But l--

156
00:06:04.624 --> 00:06:06.043
Oh. ok.

157
00:06:07.961 --> 00:06:09.418
Ugh.

158
00:06:09.533 --> 00:06:11.413
The nerve of some
of those peasants. huh?

159
00:06:11.488 --> 00:06:13.675
Tell me about it.
Aah!

160
00:06:13.790 --> 00:06:14.711
Hi there.

161
00:06:14.826 --> 00:06:16.129
Ooh. Your Highness.

162
00:06:16.206 --> 00:06:17.088
Ahem.

163
00:06:17.165 --> 00:06:19.466
Oh. oh. oh.
ha ha ha. Um...

164
00:06:19.581 --> 00:06:20.963
Uh. you were
doing it again.

165
00:06:21.040 --> 00:06:23.762
Doing? Doing...
Doing what?

166
00:06:23.877 --> 00:06:24.951
Doing my job.

167
00:06:25.028 --> 00:06:25.911
I'm the emperor.

168
00:06:25.987 --> 00:06:27.406
and you're the emperor's
advisor.

169
00:06:27.560 --> 00:06:28.365
Remember that?

170
00:06:28.517 --> 00:06:29.591
But. Your Highness.

171
00:06:29.668 --> 00:06:32.201
I was only dealing with
meaningless peasant matters.

172
00:06:32.278 --> 00:06:33.160
Whoa

173
00:06:33.237 --> 00:06:35.882
Look at these wrinkles

174
00:06:36.036 --> 00:06:38.836
What is holding
this woman together?

175
00:06:38.951 --> 00:06:40.447
What the--

176
00:06:40.524 --> 00:06:42.211
How long
has that been there?

177
00:06:42.288 --> 00:06:43.706
Good thinkin'. Yzma

178
00:06:43.783 --> 00:06:44.665
What do you say.
Kuzco?

179
00:06:44.781 --> 00:06:46.084
Whoa! No touchy!

180
00:06:46.163 --> 00:06:48.233
No touchy.
No touch.

181
00:06:48.348 --> 00:06:49.267
Excuse me.
Your Highness

182
00:06:49.345 --> 00:06:50.725
The village leader
is here to see you.

183
00:06:50.802 --> 00:06:52.298
Oh. great.
Send him in.

184
00:06:52.375 --> 00:06:53.793
Oh. and by the way.
you're fired.

185
00:06:53.870 --> 00:06:54.983
Fired?

186
00:06:55.098 --> 00:06:57.399
W-W-What do you mean.
fired?

187
00:06:57.514 --> 00:06:58.588
Um. how else
can I say it?

188
00:06:58.704 --> 00:07:00.009
You're being let go.

189
00:07:00.084 --> 00:07:01.502
your department's
being downsized.

190
00:07:01.579 --> 00:07:02.961
you're part of
an outplacement.

191
00:07:03.115 --> 00:07:04.187
we're going in a
different direction.

192
00:07:04.302 --> 00:07:05.185
we're not picking
up your option...

193
00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:06.757
Take your pick.
I got more.

194
00:07:06.911 --> 00:07:08.904
But l-- You--uh--

195
00:07:09.019 --> 00:07:10.209
Uhh.

196
00:07:10.286 --> 00:07:12.511
But--
But. Your Highness.

197
00:07:12.588 --> 00:07:15.081
I have been nothing
if not loyal to the empire

198
00:07:15.197 --> 00:07:18.072
for--for--for
many. many years.

199
00:07:18.187 --> 00:07:20.564
Hey. hey. everybody
hits their stride.

200
00:07:20.680 --> 00:07:23.365
You just hit yours
50 years ago.

201
00:07:23.442 --> 00:07:26.279
So...who's
in my chair?

202
00:07:26.394 --> 00:07:27.238
Oh. oh! I know!

203
00:07:27.353 --> 00:07:28.199
Yzma.

204
00:07:28.314 --> 00:07:29.617
Yzma's in your
chair. right?

205
00:07:29.733 --> 00:07:31.341
Very good. Kronk.

206
00:07:31.418 --> 00:07:32.454
Here. Get the snack.

207
00:07:32.531 --> 00:07:34.064
Got it!

208
00:07:34.180 --> 00:07:35.370
Unh! Oof!.

209
00:07:35.447 --> 00:07:36.329
Ok. you heard
the man.

210
00:07:36.406 --> 00:07:37.288
Up. up. up.

211
00:07:37.365 --> 00:07:39.435
I’m ok
I'm fine

212
00:07:40.892 --> 00:07:42.197
Ah.

213
00:07:43.692 --> 00:07:45.456
ok. Show him in.

214
00:07:47.565 --> 00:07:48.447
Ahem.

215
00:07:48.562 --> 00:07:50.098
Uh. afternoon.
Your Highness.

216
00:07:50.213 --> 00:07:51.860
I'm here because
I received a summons--

217
00:07:51.975 --> 00:07:52.822
Hey.
there he is!

218
00:07:52.937 --> 00:07:54.661
My main village man.

219
00:07:54.738 --> 00:07:56.081
Um. Pacha.

220
00:07:56.158 --> 00:07:57.922
Anyway. I got
this summons--

221
00:07:58.036 --> 00:07:59.379
Pacha.

222
00:07:59.495 --> 00:08:00.759
That's right.

223
00:08:00.836 --> 00:08:02.485
You are just the man
I wanted to see.

224
00:08:02.564 --> 00:08:03.752
I am?

225
00:08:03.827 --> 00:08:06.014
Word on the street is
you can fix my problem.

226
00:08:08.086 --> 00:08:10.235
You can fix my problem.
can't you?

227
00:08:10.350 --> 00:08:12.420
Sure.
I'll do what I can.

228
00:08:12.535 --> 00:08:14.913
Good. good. That's just
what I wanted to hear.

229
00:08:14.990 --> 00:08:16.639
Are you aware of
just how important

230
00:08:16.754 --> 00:08:18.019
your village is
to the empire?

231
00:08:18.096 --> 00:08:19.783
Well. I know
we grow the crops

232
00:08:19.937 --> 00:08:21.127
that you use here
at the palace.

233
00:08:21.242 --> 00:08:22.966
We also herd the llamas
that you--

234
00:08:25.805 --> 00:08:27.492
My village?

235
00:08:27.608 --> 00:08:28.528
Oh. yeah.

236
00:08:28.605 --> 00:08:30.600
You got a pretty sweet
little setup there

237
00:08:30.677 --> 00:08:33.092
on top of that hill.
don't you? Ha ha ha!

238
00:08:33.207 --> 00:08:35.471
Yeah. My family has
lived on that hilltop

239
00:08:35.548 --> 00:08:37.697
for the last
6 generations.

240
00:08:37.812 --> 00:08:38.961
Uh-huh.

241
00:08:39.076 --> 00:08:40.418
So tell me.

242
00:08:40.533 --> 00:08:42.643
where do you find
you get the most sun?

243
00:08:42.720 --> 00:08:43.831
Oh. I'd say

244
00:08:43.946 --> 00:08:46.900
just on the other side
of those trees.

245
00:08:46.977 --> 00:08:49.086
When the sun hits
that ridge just right.

246
00:08:49.201 --> 00:08:51.273
these hills sing.

247
00:08:51.349 --> 00:08:52.538
Well. that settles it.

248
00:08:52.692 --> 00:08:53.534
Really?

249
00:08:53.649 --> 00:08:54.763
Yep. Problem solved.

250
00:08:54.840 --> 00:08:55.913
Thanks for coming.

251
00:08:56.028 --> 00:08:56.910
That's it?

252
00:08:56.986 --> 00:08:58.368
That's all
you wanted me for?

253
00:08:58.482 --> 00:09:00.363
I just needed
an insider's opinion

254
00:09:00.440 --> 00:09:02.817
before I ok'd this spot
for my pool.

255
00:09:02.971 --> 00:09:05.195
Uh...your pool?

256
00:09:05.272 --> 00:09:06.153
Boo-yah!

257
00:09:06.230 --> 00:09:07.764
Welcome to
Kuzcotopia.

258
00:09:07.841 --> 00:09:09.375
my ultimate
summer getaway

259
00:09:09.528 --> 00:09:11.177
complete
with water slide.

260
00:09:11.293 --> 00:09:12.712
What?

261
00:09:12.827 --> 00:09:13.710
Isn't it great?

262
00:09:13.785 --> 00:09:15.780
It's my birthday gift
to me. Ha!

263
00:09:15.895 --> 00:09:17.506
I'm so happy.

264
00:09:17.583 --> 00:09:19.501
Uh...uh...

265
00:09:19.616 --> 00:09:22.339
um...l don't understand
how this could happen.

266
00:09:22.416 --> 00:09:24.027
Well. let me
clear it up for you.

267
00:09:24.102 --> 00:09:26.058
At my birthday
celebration tomorrow.

268
00:09:26.173 --> 00:09:27.019
I give the word.

269
00:09:27.134 --> 00:09:28.629
and your town
will be destroyed

270
00:09:28.745 --> 00:09:30.892
to make way for this...

271
00:09:36.491 --> 00:09:37.413
So. if I were you.

272
