809
00:32:02.030 --> 00:32:03.872
He's never going
to change his mind.

810
00:32:05.405 --> 00:32:08.704
Ohh. How am I ever going
to get out of here?

811
00:32:35.205 --> 00:32:36.433
And so.

812
00:32:36.510 --> 00:32:38.890
it is
with great sadness

813
00:32:38.965 --> 00:32:40.960
that we mourn
the sudden departure

814
00:32:41.075 --> 00:32:42.455
of our beloved prince...

815
00:32:43.913 --> 00:32:45.755
taken from us
so tragically

816
00:32:45.871 --> 00:32:48.592
on the very eve
of his 18th birthday.

817
00:32:48.669 --> 00:32:49.818
Poor little guy.

818
00:32:49.895 --> 00:32:52.082
His legacy will live on
in our hearts...

819
00:32:52.160 --> 00:32:53.310
He never had
a chance.

820
00:32:53.425 --> 00:32:56.071
for all eternity.

821
00:32:57.106 --> 00:32:59.295
Well. he ain't gettin'
any deader.

822
00:32:59.410 --> 00:33:00.367
Back to work.

823
00:33:13.637 --> 00:33:15.365
Kronk. darlin'.

824
00:33:15.479 --> 00:33:17.548
I must admit
you had me worried

825
00:33:17.663 --> 00:33:19.621
when you mixed up
those poisons.

826
00:33:19.696 --> 00:33:22.191
but now that
Kuzco is dead.

827
00:33:22.267 --> 00:33:23.648
all is forgiven.

828
00:33:23.763 --> 00:33:25.336
Ah. Oh. yeah. yeah.
He's...

829
00:33:25.413 --> 00:33:27.598
Heh. He's dead.
all right. Heh heh.

830
00:33:27.674 --> 00:33:29.784
I mean. you can't get
much deader than he--

831
00:33:29.898 --> 00:33:31.318
than he is right now.

832
00:33:31.433 --> 00:33:33.542
Unless. of course.
we killed him again.

833
00:33:33.657 --> 00:33:36.383
I suppose.

834
00:33:36.459 --> 00:33:38.682
Hey. look.
the royal dresser's here.

835
00:33:38.759 --> 00:33:39.987
Kronk...

836
00:33:41.329 --> 00:33:42.787
I should tell you right now
I'm kind of hard to fit.

837
00:33:42.864 --> 00:33:43.746
Kronk...

838
00:33:43.823 --> 00:33:46.813
I wear a 66 long
and a 31 waist.

839
00:33:46.890 --> 00:33:49.691
Kuzco is dead. right?

840
00:33:49.768 --> 00:33:51.186
Tell me Kuzco's dead.

841
00:33:51.262 --> 00:33:54.330
I need to hear
these words.

842
00:33:54.406 --> 00:33:56.978
Do you need to hear
all those words exactly?

843
00:33:57.093 --> 00:33:58.473
He's still alive?

844
00:33:58.549 --> 00:34:00.814
Well. he's not as dead
as we would've hoped.

845
00:34:00.929 --> 00:34:02.232
Kronk...

846
00:34:02.308 --> 00:34:04.189
I just thought
I'd give you the heads-up

847
00:34:04.304 --> 00:34:05.684
in case Kuzco
ever came back.

848
00:34:05.838 --> 00:34:07.601
He can't come back!

849
00:34:07.717 --> 00:34:09.519
Yeah. That would be
kind of awkward--

850
00:34:09.635 --> 00:34:11.360
especially after
that lovely eulogy.

851
00:34:11.514 --> 00:34:12.934
You think?

852
00:34:13.048 --> 00:34:14.889
You and I are going out
to find him.

853
00:34:15.003 --> 00:34:16.655
If he talks.
we are through!

854
00:34:16.769 --> 00:34:17.804
Now let's move!

855
00:34:18.572 --> 00:34:19.760
Dad. look out!

856
00:34:20.987 --> 00:34:22.597
Tipo. what is it?

857
00:34:22.751 --> 00:34:24.630
I had a dream that
Dad was tied to a log

858
00:34:24.706 --> 00:34:26.242
and was careening
out of control

859
00:34:26.356 --> 00:34:28.351
down a raging river
of death!

860
00:34:28.465 --> 00:34:29.655
All right. all right.
it's ok.

861
00:34:29.769 --> 00:34:30.806
- It was awful!
- Shh!

862
00:34:30.884 --> 00:34:32.416
It's ok. it's ok.
Tipo. calm down.

863
00:34:32.532 --> 00:34:33.989
It was just a dream.

864
00:34:34.105 --> 00:34:35.179
Your dad's fine.

865
00:34:35.255 --> 00:34:36.902
He just went back
to see the emperor.

866
00:34:38.554 --> 00:34:40.586
Oh. Like you
told him to.

867
00:34:40.663 --> 00:34:41.967
'cause you're
always right.

868
00:34:42.081 --> 00:34:43.309
That's right.

869
00:34:43.385 --> 00:34:45.036
Well. in my dream.
Dad had to kiss a llama.

870
00:34:45.112 --> 00:34:46.914
Yeah. like that
would ever happen.

871
00:34:47.068 --> 00:34:48.601
- It could.
- Nuh-uh.

872
00:34:48.717 --> 00:34:49.905
- Yeah-huh.
- Nuh-uh.

873
00:34:49.983 --> 00:34:51.210
Yeah-huh.

874
00:34:53.664 --> 00:34:54.547
Good night. you two.

875
00:34:54.623 --> 00:34:55.583
- Night. Mom!
- Night. Mom!

876
00:34:55.697 --> 00:34:57.385
- Yeah-huh. Yeah-huh.
- Nuh-uh. Nuh-uh.

877
00:35:03.061 --> 00:35:05.324
Ooh!

878
00:35:07.128 --> 00:35:08.048
B-B-Brr!

879
00:35:08.125 --> 00:35:09.927
Uh. hey

880
00:35:14.606 --> 00:35:15.603
Thanks.

881
00:35:15.719 --> 00:35:17.597
Oh.

882
00:35:17.713 --> 00:35:19.094
No problem.

883
00:35:20.704 --> 00:35:21.969
Feels like wool.

884
00:35:22.047 --> 00:35:23.199
Yeah.

885
00:35:23.275 --> 00:35:24.501
Alpaca?

886
00:35:24.577 --> 00:35:25.920
Oh. yeah. it is.

887
00:35:25.998 --> 00:35:28.490
Oh. yeah.
I thought so.

888
00:35:28.567 --> 00:35:29.793
It's nice.

889
00:35:29.909 --> 00:35:31.329
My wife made it.

890
00:35:31.443 --> 00:35:32.632
Oh. she knits?

891
00:35:32.710 --> 00:35:34.282
Crochets.

892
00:35:34.396 --> 00:35:36.429
Crochets?
Nice.

893
00:35:36.545 --> 00:35:38.193
Thanks.

894
00:35:43.373 --> 00:35:45.097
So...

895
00:35:45.213 --> 00:35:49.431
So. I was thinking that
when I got back to the city.

896
00:35:49.547 --> 00:35:50.735
we'd. uh...

897
00:35:50.813 --> 00:35:51.887
I mean. there's
lots of hilltops.

898
00:35:51.963 --> 00:35:54.456
and maybe I might.
you know...

899
00:35:54.572 --> 00:35:55.684
I--I might...

900
00:35:55.760 --> 00:35:58.559
Are you saying...

901
00:35:58.637 --> 00:36:00.094
you've changed
your mind?

902
00:36:00.210 --> 00:36:01.858
Oh. well. l--I...

903
00:36:02.012 --> 00:36:03.277
Because you know
that means

904
00:36:03.393 --> 00:36:06.115
you're doing something
nice for someone else.

905
00:36:06.193 --> 00:36:07.918
No. I know that.
I know.

906
00:36:08.036 --> 00:36:09.836
And you're all right
with that?

907
00:36:09.952 --> 00:36:10.795
Yes.

908
00:36:16.971 --> 00:36:17.929
What?

909
00:36:20.882 --> 00:36:22.992
Don't shake
unless you mean it.

910
00:36:30.586 --> 00:36:31.927
All right.

911
00:36:33.501 --> 00:36:35.918
Let's get you
back to the palace.

912
00:36:35.994 --> 00:36:38.409
Oh. by the way.
thanks.

913
00:36:38.563 --> 00:36:40.365
No...

914
00:36:40.443 --> 00:36:42.014
thank you.

915
00:36:54.173 --> 00:36:55.784
Ok.
Once we cross this bridge.

916
00:36:55.860 --> 00:36:57.204
it's only an hour
to the palace.

917
00:36:57.280 --> 00:36:58.585
Good. because
believe it or not.

918
00:36:58.699 --> 00:36:59.773
I think I need a bath.

919
00:36:59.851 --> 00:37:00.733
I believe it.

920
00:37:00.809 --> 00:37:02.112
- What was that?
- Nothing.

921
00:37:02.228 --> 00:37:03.684
Ohh!

922
00:37:03.838 --> 00:37:05.143
Whoa!

923
00:37:05.257 --> 00:37:06.255
Kuzco!

924
00:37:07.827 --> 00:37:09.208
Kuzco!

925
00:37:09.284 --> 00:37:10.704
- Yeah?
- Quick. help me up!

926
00:37:12.737 --> 00:37:14.425
No. I don't think
I will.

927
00:37:14.539 --> 00:37:15.806
You're going
to leave me here?

928
00:37:15.920 --> 00:37:17.952
Well. I was going to have
you imprisoned for life.

929
00:37:18.068 --> 00:37:19.525
but I kind of
like this better.

930
00:37:19.679 --> 00:37:21.672
I thought you were
a changed man.

931
00:37:21.750 --> 00:37:22.710
Oh. come on.
I had to say something

932
00:37:22.824 --> 00:37:24.396
to get you to take me
back to the city.

933
00:37:24.472 --> 00:37:26.237
So all of it
was a lie?

934
00:37:26.315 --> 00:37:28.271
Well. yeah.
No. wait.

935
00:37:30.340 --> 00:37:32.414
Uh. yeah. yeah.
It all was a lie.

936
00:37:32.528 --> 00:37:34.099
Toodles.

937
00:37:34.215 --> 00:37:35.597
We shook hands on it!

938
00:37:39.393 --> 00:37:42.001
You know. the funny thing
about shaking hands is...

939
00:37:42.079 --> 00:37:43.612
you need hands.

940
00:37:43.688 --> 00:37:45.108
Ha! ok.

941
00:37:45.222 --> 00:37:46.757
Buh-bye.

942
00:37:46.871 --> 00:37:48.061
Aah!

943
00:37:48.139 --> 00:37:49.634
Are you ok?
Are you all right?

944
00:37:49.748 --> 00:37:51.090
Yeah.

945
00:37:51.168 --> 00:37:52.088
Yeah. I think
I'm all right.

946
00:37:52.166 --> 00:37:53.853
Good!

947
00:37:53.967 --> 00:37:55.657
That's for going back
on your promise!

948
00:37:55.771 --> 00:37:56.882
Yii!

949
00:37:56.998 --> 00:37:58.914
Yeah. That's for
kidnapping me

950
00:37:59.028 --> 00:38:00.259
and taking me
to your village...

951
00:38:00.335 --> 00:38:02.061
which I'm still gonna
destroy. by the way.

952
00:38:02.175 --> 00:38:04.016
Ah ha ha ha!
No touchy.

953
00:38:04.132 --> 00:38:04.976
Ooh!

954
00:38:05.090 --> 00:38:06.202
Why did I risk my life

955
00:38:06.317 --> 00:38:07.853
for a selfish brat
like you?

956
00:38:07.967 --> 00:38:09.809
I was always taught that there
was some good in everyone.

957
00:38:09.885 --> 00:38:11.456
but. ooh.
you proved me wrong.

958
00:38:11.532 --> 00:38:13.527
Oh. boohoo.
Now I feel really bad.

959
00:38:13.605 --> 00:38:14.641
Bad llama.

960
00:38:14.717 --> 00:38:16.137
I could've let you die
out there in that jungle.

961
00:38:16.251 --> 00:38:17.824
and then all my problems
would be over.

962
00:38:17.900 --> 00:38:20.088
Well. that makes you
ugly and stupid.

963
00:38:20.164 --> 00:38:21.277
Let's end this.

964
00:38:21.391 --> 00:38:22.465
Ladies first.

965
00:38:22.543 --> 00:38:25.494
- Aah! - Yaah!

966
00:38:32.590 --> 00:38:33.434
Ohh!

967
00:38:37.882 --> 00:38:39.456
- Aah!
- Aah!

968
00:38:40.913 --> 00:38:42.217
- Ow! Ow!
- Ow! Ow!

969
00:38:42.295 --> 00:38:45.132
- Whoa!
- Ohh!

970
00:38:48.047 --> 00:38:49.007
What are we
gonna do?

971
00:38:49.775 --> 00:38:51.115
Aah!

972
00:38:51.193 --> 00:38:52.726
What are we gonna do?
We're gonna die!

973
00:38:52.840 --> 00:38:56.063
We're gonna die!
That's it for me!

974
00:38:56.177 --> 00:38:57.061
No. we're not

975
00:38:57.137 --> 00:38:58.748
Calm down.

976
00:38:58.824 --> 00:39:01.663
I have an idea.
Give me your arm.

977
00:39:01.777 --> 00:39:04.079
Ok. now
the other one.

978
00:39:05.384 --> 00:39:08.068
When I say go.
push against my back.

979
00:39:08.143 --> 00:39:10.025
and we'll walk
up the hill.

980
00:39:10.101 --> 00:39:11.137
Ready?

981
00:39:11.251 --> 00:39:12.134
Go.

982
00:39:12.210 --> 00:39:13.092
Ow!

983
00:39:13.168 --> 00:39:15.356
You did that
on purpose.

984
00:39:15.471 --> 00:39:17.581
- Aah!
- No. I didn't!

985
00:39:17.733 --> 00:39:18.844
Now. we're gonna have
to work together

986
00:39:18.960 --> 00:39:20.838
to get out of this.
so follow my lead.

987
00:39:20.916 --> 00:39:22.143
Ready?

988
00:39:22.221 --> 00:39:23.293
- Right foot.
- Whose right?

989
00:39:23.409 --> 00:39:24.791
Your right
or mine?

990
00:39:24.905 --> 00:39:25.940
I don't care.
Mine.

991
00:39:26.018 --> 00:39:27.130
Well. why yours?

992
00:39:27.208 --> 00:39:28.280
Ok. your right!
Ready?

993
00:39:28.396 --> 00:39:29.239
Ok. got it.

994
00:39:29.355 --> 00:39:31.005
Ok. right.

995
00:39:31.119 --> 00:39:32.690
Left. Right.

996
00:39:32.768 --> 00:39:35.146
Ha ha!
Look. we're moving!

997
00:39:36.181 --> 00:39:37.063
Aah!

998
00:39:37.139 --> 00:39:38.751
Don't look down!
Now. stay with me.

999
00:39:38.829 --> 00:39:39.710
Stay with me.

1000
00:39:39.788 --> 00:39:41.436
Right. Left.

1001
00:39:41.550 --> 00:39:43.201
Right. Left.

1002
00:39:43.315 --> 00:39:45.387
Right. Left.

1003
00:39:45.501 --> 00:39:47.074
Right!

1004
00:39:47.150 --> 00:39:49.681
Now what. genius?

1005
00:39:49.759 --> 00:39:51.483
Working on it.

1006
00:39:51.599 --> 00:39:53.670
Ok. here's the deal.

1007
00:39:53.748 --> 00:39:55.168
Stretch out your neck.

1008
00:39:55.282 --> 00:39:56.778
and I'll grab the rope.

1009
00:39:56.893 --> 00:39:58.273
How do I know
you won't let me fall

1010
00:39:58.349 --> 00:39:59.425
after you grab
the rope?

1011
00:39:59.501 --> 00:40:02.376
You're just gonna
have to trust me!

1012
00:40:05.061 --> 00:40:06.711
You know.
it's a good thing

1013
00:40:06.827 --> 00:40:08.092
you're not
a big. fat guy.

1014
00:40:08.246 --> 00:40:10.010
or this would be
really difficult.

1015
00:40:10.125 --> 00:40:11.967
Aah! Aah!

1016
00:40:12.081 --> 00:40:13.347
Almost.

1017
00:40:13.422 --> 00:40:14.688
Got it!

1018
00:40:15.802 --> 00:40:16.836
It's stuck.

1019
00:40:16.914 --> 00:40:19.791
Take your time.
No hurry here.

1020
00:40:21.056 --> 00:40:22.514
Scorpions!
Aah ha ha!

1021
00:40:22.628 --> 00:40:23.510
Kuzco!

1022
00:40:23.625 --> 00:40:24.777
Aah!

1023
00:40:24.891 --> 00:40:26.423
Oh. no!

1024
00:40:29.456 --> 00:40:30.336
Uhh!

1025
00:40:30.414 --> 00:40:32.677
Aah!

1026
00:40:32.753 --> 00:40:34.786
Ooh! Ooh! Ooh! Ooh!

1027
00:40:34.902 --> 00:40:36.244
Huh?

1028
00:40:37.434 --> 00:40:39.771
Aah!

1029
00:40:39.849 --> 00:40:41.344
Aah!

1030
00:40:41.422 --> 00:40:44.568
Whoa!

1031
00:40:52.275 --> 00:40:54.461
- Huh?

1032
00:40:54.577 --> 00:40:56.378
Look out!

1033
00:40:56.456 --> 00:40:57.760
Ohh!

1034
00:40:57.876 --> 00:41:00.061
Pacha: Ohh

1035
00:41:00.137 --> 00:41:01.789
Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

1036
00:41:01.865 --> 00:41:03.206
Ooh. look at me
and my bad self.

1037
00:41:03.284 --> 00:41:05.931
I snatched you
right out of the air.

1038
00:41:06.007 --> 00:41:07.809
"Ooh. I'm
a crumbly canyon wall.

1039
00:41:07.923 --> 00:41:09.460
and I'm taking you
with me."

1040
00:41:09.536 --> 00:41:10.456
Well. not today. pal.

1041
00:41:10.532 --> 00:41:11.568
Uh-huh.

1042
00:41:11.644 --> 00:41:13.139
Uh-huh. uh-huh. uh-huh.

1043
00:41:13.217 --> 00:41:14.099
Uh-huh

1044
00:41:14.177 --> 00:41:16.132
You just saved my life.

1045
00:41:16.248 --> 00:41:17.130
Huh?

1046
00:41:18.510 --> 00:41:19.431
So?

1047
00:41:19.507 --> 00:41:20.657
- I knew it.
- Knew what?

1048
00:41:20.733 --> 00:41:21.961
That there is some good
in you after all.

1049
00:41:22.039 --> 00:41:22.920
Oh. no
- Admit it.

1050
00:41:22.998 --> 00:41:24.226
- Wrong.
- Yes. there is.

1051
00:41:24.340 --> 00:41:25.605
- Nuh-uh.
- I think there is.

1052
00:41:25.682 --> 00:41:27.255
- Hey. you could've let me fall.
- Nuh-uh!

1053
00:41:27.369 --> 00:41:28.367
Come on.
what's the big deal?

1054
00:41:28.443 --> 00:41:30.094
Nobody's that heartless.

1055
00:41:31.820 --> 00:41:33.659
Don't read
too much into it.

1056
00:41:33.735 --> 00:41:35.193
It was a one-time thing.

1057
00:41:35.309 --> 00:41:37.648
Right. Sure.

1058
00:41:37.726 --> 00:41:39.606
Well. we better get going.

1059
00:41:39.721 --> 00:41:40.793
With that bridge out.

1060
00:41:40.869 --> 00:41:42.135
it's a 4-daywalk
to the palace.

1061
00:41:42.213 --> 00:41:43.902
What?

1062
00:41:44.016 --> 00:41:45.320
You mean you're still
taking me back?

1063
00:41:45.396 --> 00:41:46.817
I shook on it.
didn't I?

1064
00:41:46.893 --> 00:41:49.001
Well. yeah.
but I hope you realize

1065
00:41:49.117 --> 00:41:50.304
that doesn't
change a thing.

1066
00:41:50.380 --> 00:41:52.186
I'm still building
Kuzcotopia

1067
00:41:52.262 --> 00:41:53.181
when I get back.

1068
00:41:53.259 --> 00:41:54.755
Well. 4 days
is a long time.

1069
00:41:54.831 --> 00:41:56.365
Who knows? Maybe
you'll change your mind.

1070
00:41:56.481 --> 00:41:57.362
Uh-huh.

1071
00:41:57.440 --> 00:41:59.052
4 days.

1072
00:41:59.128 --> 00:42:00.853
What are the chances
of you carrying me?

1073
00:42:00.967 --> 00:42:02.309
Not good.

1074
00:42:04.496 --> 00:42:06.568
No. no. no!

1075
00:42:06.682 --> 00:42:07.795
We've searched
every village

1076
00:42:07.911 --> 00:42:09.099
surrounding the palace

1077
00:42:09.177 --> 00:42:10.900
and still
no sign of Kuzco.

1078
00:42:11.016 --> 00:42:13.050
Where is he?

1079
00:42:13.126 --> 00:42:14.010
Kronk!

1080
00:42:14.085 --> 00:42:15.119
Kronk here.

1081
00:42:15.197 --> 00:42:16.961
I'm getting tired.
Pull over.

1082
00:42:17.077 --> 00:42:18.302
Sure thing.
Kronk out.

1083
00:42:23.059 --> 00:42:24.862
Ooh! Aah!

1084
00:42:24.978 --> 00:42:26.052
Aah! Ohh!

1085
00:42:29.849 --> 00:42:30.960
Perfect.

1086
00:42:31.036 --> 00:42:33.724
These are my best shoes.

1087
00:42:35.371 --> 00:42:37.942
I hate this jungle.

1088
00:42:39.054 --> 00:42:40.626
Oh. look.

1089
00:42:40.742 --> 00:42:42.659
A golden-throated
small-winged warbler.

1090
00:42:42.811 --> 00:42:44.653
Just one more
for exotic bird bingo.

1091
00:42:44.730 --> 00:42:45.612
Aah!

1092
00:42:45.688 --> 00:42:47.262
I am loving this.

1093
00:42:55.391 --> 00:42:57.041
Get away from me!

1094
00:42:57.119 --> 00:42:58.536
Uhh

1095
00:43:00.570 --> 00:43:01.606
Yeah.
Tell me about it.

1096
00:43:03.409 --> 00:43:04.713
No. no.
it's not you.

1097
00:43:04.789 --> 00:43:06.938
She's not the easiest
person to get close to.

1098
00:43:07.014 --> 00:43:09.315
There's a wall there.
Trust me.

1099
00:43:09.431 --> 00:43:11.347
Are you talking
to that squirrel?

1100
00:43:11.463 --> 00:43:13.418
I was a junior chipmunk.

1101
00:43:13.534 --> 00:43:15.949
I had to be versed in
all the woodland creatures.

1102
00:43:16.065 --> 00:43:17.025
Please continue.

1103
00:43:19.478 --> 00:43:20.590
Aah!

1104
00:43:20.668 --> 00:43:22.164
Why me?

1105
00:43:22.240 --> 00:43:23.391
Why me?

1106
00:43:23.505 --> 00:43:25.615
Hey. it doesn't always
have to be about you.

1107
00:43:25.731 --> 00:43:27.494
This poor little guy
has had it rough.

1108
00:43:27.610 --> 00:43:28.762
Seems a talking llama

1109
00:43:28.876 --> 00:43:30.641
Kronk: gave him a hard
time the other day

1110
00:43:30.717 --> 00:43:33.094
Oh. a talking llama?

1111
00:43:33.208 --> 00:43:34.820
Ha ha ha ha!
Do tell.

1112
00:43:34.936 --> 00:43:35.932
Heh heh heh heh!

1113
00:43:37.697 --> 00:43:39.998
Uh. he doesn't really
want to talk to you.

1114
00:43:40.074 --> 00:43:42.070
Well. then
you ask him.

1115
00:43:43.181 --> 00:43:44.257
I hate being
in the middle.

1116
00:43:44.371 --> 00:43:45.559
Squeaky. uh...

1117
00:43:45.635 --> 00:43:47.400
squeak. squeaker.
squeakin'.

1118
00:43:48.782 --> 00:43:50.047
Aah!

1119
00:43:50.201 --> 00:43:52.157
Jaguars? No kidding?
Brutal.

1120
00:43:58.907 --> 00:44:00.710
Uh. could you give us
a little room here?

1121
00:44:00.786 --> 00:44:01.976
Uh. sorry.

1122
00:44:03.893 --> 00:44:05.043
Uh-uh.

1123
00:44:05.197 --> 00:44:07.498
A little bit more.
please.

1124
00:44:07.574 --> 00:44:09.454
How is this?

1125
00:44:09.568 --> 00:44:10.567
- Yeah. that's good.

1126
00:44:10.681 --> 00:44:14.172
Now ask him which way
the talking llama went!

1127
00:44:14.286 --> 00:44:17.661
Uh. squeakity-squeak.
squeakin'.

1128
00:44:28.748 --> 00:44:29.820
Low blood sugar. huh?

1129
00:44:29.896 --> 00:44:31.661
Yeah.
It's a curse. Ha.

1130
00:44:31.777 --> 00:44:33.003
Well. as soon as we get
something to eat.

1131
00:44:33.081 --> 00:44:34.652
you're walking
the rest of the way.

1132
00:44:45.507 --> 00:44:47.807
Welcome to Mudka's Meat Hut.

1133
00:44:47.885 --> 00:44:49.534
home of the mug...

1134
00:44:51.414 --> 00:44:53.985
...of meat.
What'll it be?

1135
00:44:54.099 --> 00:44:56.478
Ahem. We'll have
2 specials.

1136
00:44:56.630 --> 00:44:58.202
Is that all right.
dear?

1137
00:44:58.277 --> 00:45:00.695
Oh. whatever you say. pumpkin.
You know what I like.

1138
00:45:00.811 --> 00:45:02.996
Hee hee hee. We're
on our honeymoon.

1139
00:45:03.072 --> 00:45:06.141
Bless you for
coming out in public.

1140
00:45:06.257 --> 00:45:08.213
So that's 2 specials.

1141
00:45:08.329 --> 00:45:11.396
And an onion log.
To split.

1142
00:45:12.853 --> 00:45:15.001
Ordering!
I need 2 heartburns

1143
00:45:15.077 --> 00:45:18.184
and a deep-fried doorstop
on table 12!

1144
00:45:20.601 --> 00:45:22.672
Ok. so I'll admit
this was a good idea.

1145
00:45:22.750 --> 00:45:25.740
When will you learn that
all my ideas are good ones?

1146
00:45:25.818 --> 00:45:27.159
That's funny.

1147
00:45:27.235 --> 00:45:29.117
because I thought that you
going into the jungle by yourself.

1148
00:45:29.193 --> 00:45:30.572
being chased by jaguars.

1149
00:45:30.650 --> 00:45:32.106
lying to me to take you
back to the palace

1150
00:45:32.222 --> 00:45:33.949
were all really bad ideas.

1151
00:45:34.101 --> 00:45:36.556
Anything sounds bad when
you say it with that attitude.

1152
00:45:36.672 --> 00:45:41.581
Hot and crispy pill bug
for the happy couple.

1153
00:45:41.659 --> 00:45:42.539
Mazeltov

1154
00:45:45.646 --> 00:45:48.023
Oh. boy.

1155
00:45:49.481 --> 00:45:53.278
Ooh. Ugh. Bluh.

1156
00:45:53.356 --> 00:45:54.467
Urp!

1157
00:45:54.583 --> 00:45:56.846
Oh. here
Let me get that for you

1158
00:45:56.960 --> 00:45:59.262
Bleaggh! Uck!

1159
00:46:00.451 --> 00:46:01.333
Where are you going?

1160
00:46:01.447 --> 00:46:02.753
I'm just going to slip
into the kitchen

1161
00:46:02.869 --> 00:46:03.789
and have a word
with the chef.

1162
00:46:03.865 --> 00:46:05.398
You're gonna get us
thrown out.

1163
00:46:05.474 --> 00:46:07.853
Please.
With this disguise.

1164
00:46:07.929 --> 00:46:09.809
I'm invisible.

1165
00:46:13.952 --> 00:46:14.795
Heh heh!

1166
00:46:14.911 --> 00:46:16.713
We've been walking
around in circles

1167
00:46:16.829 --> 00:46:18.132
for who knows how long.

1168
00:46:18.208 --> 00:46:20.050
That is the last time

1169
00:46:20.126 --> 00:46:21.891
we take directions
from a squirrel.

1170
00:46:21.967 --> 00:46:23.809
I should have done away
with Kuzco myself

1171
00:46:23.887 --> 00:46:25.150
when I had the chance.

1172
00:46:27.568 --> 00:46:30.405
Oh. you really gotta stop
beating yourself up about that.

1173
00:46:32.822 --> 00:46:35.315
Uh-oh I'll get you
another one there. Yzma

1174
00:46:36.351 --> 00:46:38.115
You using
that fork there. pal?

1175
00:46:38.231 --> 00:46:39.188
Hey. don't I know you?

1176
00:46:39.304 --> 00:46:40.186
I don't think so.

1177
00:46:40.262 --> 00:46:41.643
Wrestled you
in high school?

1178
00:46:41.721 --> 00:46:42.985
Don't remember that.

1179
00:46:43.063 --> 00:46:44.061
Metal shop? I got it!

1180
00:46:44.175 --> 00:46:46.016
Miss Narca's interpretive
dance--2 semesters.

1181
00:46:46.092 --> 00:46:48.777
I was usually in the back
because of my weak ankles.

1182
00:46:48.853 --> 00:46:50.541
Come on. pal.
You gotta help me out here.

1183
00:46:50.657 --> 00:46:52.268
I don't think
we've ever met.

1184
00:46:52.344 --> 00:46:53.458
but I gotta go.

1185
00:46:53.572 --> 00:46:54.606
Don't worry.
I'll think of it.

1186
00:46:54.722 --> 00:46:57.253
Look. all I know is
the food looked iffy.

1187
00:46:57.369 --> 00:46:59.210
I'm not the only one
that thinks that. I'm sure.

1188
00:46:59.324 --> 00:47:00.168
Psst! Hey!

1189
00:47:00.284 --> 00:47:02.123
So I'm just
checking to make sure

1190
00:47:02.201 --> 00:47:03.811
you're going to take
the main course up a notch.

1191
00:47:03.887 --> 00:47:06.228
Is there anything
on this menu

1192
00:47:06.306 --> 00:47:07.494
that is not
swimming in gravy?

1193
00:47:07.608 --> 00:47:08.876
Hang on.
I'll go ask the chef.

1194
00:47:08.990 --> 00:47:10.717
It's a simple
question.

1195
00:47:10.793 --> 00:47:12.672
Is there or is there
not anything edible...

1196
00:47:12.786 --> 00:47:13.976
- on this menu?
- Gah!

1197
00:47:16.277 --> 00:47:18.809
Hey. I didn't ask him
about dessert yet!

1198
00:47:18.885 --> 00:47:21.188
Hey. pal. what's your policy
on making special orders?

1199
00:47:21.302 --> 00:47:23.373
All right. buster.
that's it!

1200
00:47:23.487 --> 00:47:24.793
You want a special order.
then you make it!

1201
00:47:24.869 --> 00:47:25.789
I quit!

1202
00:47:25.865 --> 00:47:27.208
Yeah. but l--

1203
00:47:27.284 --> 00:47:28.820
I try and I try.
but there's no respect

1204
00:47:28.934 --> 00:47:30.275
for anyone with vision.
That's it!

1205
00:47:30.391 --> 00:47:31.809
There's just nothing
I can do about it!

1206
00:47:31.925 --> 00:47:32.806
Please don't go.

1207
00:47:32.923 --> 00:47:35.186
3 pork combos.
extra bacon on the side.

1208
00:47:35.262 --> 00:47:36.873
2 chili cheese
samplers.

1209
00:47:36.987 --> 00:47:38.523
a basket of
liver and onion rings.

1210
00:47:38.637 --> 00:47:39.978
a catch of the day.

1211
00:47:40.056 --> 00:47:42.090
and a steak cut
in the shape of a trout.

1212
00:47:42.204 --> 00:47:43.356
You got all that. honey?

1213
00:47:43.471 --> 00:47:45.079
3 oinkers wearing pants.
plate of hot air.

1214
00:47:45.233 --> 00:47:46.577
basket of
grandma's breakfast.

1215
00:47:46.653 --> 00:47:47.728
and change the bull
to a gill. got it.

1216
00:47:47.844 --> 00:47:48.802
What's going on?

1217
00:47:48.954 --> 00:47:50.336
No time to explain.
We gotta get out of here.

1218
00:47:50.414 --> 00:47:53.748
What is he
doing in there?

1219
00:47:56.510 --> 00:47:57.583
Unh! Come on!

1220
00:47:57.699 --> 00:47:59.349
In a minute.
I'm still hungry.

1221
00:47:59.425 --> 00:48:00.576
No. Kuzco!

1222
00:48:00.652 --> 00:48:02.188
Ok. I'll make it simple
for you.

1223
00:48:02.264 --> 00:48:03.952
I'll have a spinach omelet
with wheat toast.

1224
00:48:04.028 --> 00:48:05.371
- You got it?
- Can do.

1225
00:48:05.447 --> 00:48:07.824
What's taking so long?

1226
00:48:07.902 --> 00:48:08.822
Pickup!

1227
00:48:08.898 --> 00:48:10.358
Kronk!
What are you doing?

1228
00:48:10.510 --> 00:48:11.431
Kinda busy here.

1229
00:48:11.545 --> 00:48:12.541
Why am I
not surprised?

1230
00:48:12.657 --> 00:48:13.617
Your order's up!

1231
00:48:13.731 --> 00:48:15.228
Ohh!

1232
00:48:15.344 --> 00:48:17.605
Oh. well.
while you're at it.

1233
00:48:17.719 --> 00:48:19.523
make me the special.
And hold the gravy!

1234
00:48:19.637 --> 00:48:20.519
Check. Pickup!

1235
00:48:20.635 --> 00:48:21.976
You know what?
On second thought.

1236
00:48:22.092 --> 00:48:23.090
make my omelet
a meat pie.

1237
00:48:23.206 --> 00:48:24.088
Meat pie Check

1238
00:48:24.164 --> 00:48:25.045
Kronk!

1239
00:48:26.235 --> 00:48:28.422
Can I order the potatoes
as a side dish?

1240
00:48:28.498 --> 00:48:29.456
I'll have to charge you
full price.

1241
00:48:29.572 --> 00:48:30.532
Ooh!

1242
00:48:30.608 --> 00:48:32.295
Hey. how about a side
of potatoes. my buddy?

1243
00:48:32.371 --> 00:48:33.559
You got it. Want cheese
on those potatoes?

1244
00:48:33.637 --> 00:48:35.056
Thank you. Kronk.
Cheddar will be fine.

1245
00:48:35.170 --> 00:48:36.284
Cheddar spuds
coming up.

1246
00:48:36.360 --> 00:48:37.242
Spuds yes.
cheese no.

1247
00:48:37.318 --> 00:48:38.239
Hold the cheese.

1248
00:48:38.355 --> 00:48:39.199
No. I want
the cheese

1249
00:48:39.313 --> 00:48:40.427
Cheese me
no like.

1250
00:48:40.503 --> 00:48:41.538
- Cheese out.
- Cheese in!

1251
00:48:41.614 --> 00:48:42.496
Come on.
make up your mind!

1252
00:48:42.572 --> 00:48:43.688
Ok. ok.
on second thought...

1253
00:48:43.802 --> 00:48:45.222
Make
my potatoes a salad.

1254
00:49:01.751 --> 00:49:02.940
Excuse me. You see
that woman over there?

1255
00:49:04.820 --> 00:49:07.005
No problem. hon.
We do that all the time.

1256
00:49:12.146 --> 00:49:13.105
Waiters: 1. 2. 3. 4

1257
00:49:13.259 --> 00:49:14.063
Happy. happy birthday

1258
00:49:14.215 --> 00:49:15.557
From all of us to you

1259
00:49:15.672 --> 00:49:16.516
We wish
it was our birthday

1260
00:49:16.632 --> 00:49:17.936
So we could party. too

1261
00:49:18.052 --> 00:49:19.317
Happy. happy birthday

1262
00:49:19.393 --> 00:49:20.353
May all your dreams
come true

1263
00:49:20.469 --> 00:49:23.306
Ha ha ha!
It's your birthday?

1264
00:49:25.264 --> 00:49:26.452
What are you doing?

1265
00:49:26.567 --> 00:49:28.445
Look. there's 2 people
in there looking for you.

1266
00:49:28.561 --> 00:49:29.443
What?

1267
00:49:29.518 --> 00:49:30.592
A big guy
and a skinny old woman.

1268
00:49:30.708 --> 00:49:32.742
Wait. Was this woman
scary beyond all reason?

1269
00:49:32.896 --> 00:49:33.739
Oh. yeah.

1270
00:49:33.891 --> 00:49:35.465
That's Yzma and Kronk!
I'm saved!

1271
00:49:35.579 --> 00:49:37.612
Trust me. they're
not here to save you.

1272
00:49:37.728 --> 00:49:38.840
They'll take me back
to the palace.

1273
00:49:38.954 --> 00:49:40.527
Thanks for your help.
You've been great.

1274
00:49:40.643 --> 00:49:41.715
I can take it from here.

1275
00:49:41.793 --> 00:49:44.170
You don't understand.
They're trying to kill you.

1276
00:49:44.284 --> 00:49:45.972
Kill me? Their whole world
revolves around me.

1277
00:49:46.088 --> 00:49:47.277
No. I can't let you!

1278
00:49:47.353 --> 00:49:49.271
What? Wha--

1279
00:49:49.349 --> 00:49:51.036
Oh. I get it!

1280
00:49:51.150 --> 00:49:52.110
What?

1281
00:49:52.224 --> 00:49:53.606
You don't want to take me
back to the palace.

1282
00:49:53.722 --> 00:49:55.485
You want to keep me
stranded out here forever.

1283
00:49:55.561 --> 00:49:56.635
No!

1284
00:49:56.750 --> 00:49:58.170
This has all been an act.
and I almost fell for it.

1285
00:49:58.246 --> 00:49:59.320
Will you just
listen to me--

1286
00:49:59.396 --> 00:50:00.586
No. no.
you listen to me.

1287
00:50:00.664 --> 00:50:03.539
All you care about
is your stupid hilltop!

1288
00:50:03.655 --> 00:50:04.766
What?

1289
00:50:04.842 --> 00:50:06.302
You don't care about me.
Now. just get out of here.

1290
00:50:06.378 --> 00:50:07.260
- Go!
- But--

1291
00:50:07.336 --> 00:50:09.369
Go on! Get outta here!

1292
00:50:09.445 --> 00:50:11.746
Fine! Hmph!

1293
00:50:11.824 --> 00:50:13.818
Oh. this entire mess
is all your fault.

1294
00:50:13.894 --> 00:50:15.239
What'd I do?

1295
00:50:15.353 --> 00:50:17.269
If you hadn't mixed up
those poisons.

1296
00:50:17.385 --> 00:50:18.842
Kuzco would be dead now!

1297
00:50:18.958 --> 00:50:20.798
There'll be
no more diversions

1298
00:50:20.876 --> 00:50:23.331
until we track that
llama down and kill him!

1299
00:50:23.483 --> 00:50:25.362
Said I was sorry.
Can't just let it go.

1300
00:50:25.440 --> 00:50:27.472
Not even
on your birthday.

1301
00:50:27.588 --> 00:50:29.773
Kuzco must be eliminated.

1302
00:50:29.889 --> 00:50:32.612
The empire will finally be
rid of that useless slug.

1303
00:50:32.728 --> 00:50:34.530
Well. you've got a point.

1304
00:50:34.682 --> 00:50:37.407
Nobody really seems to care
that he's gone. do they?

1305
00:50:38.940 --> 00:50:40.590
Pacha!

1306
00:50:45.422 --> 00:50:46.880
Pacha?

1307
00:51:22.856 --> 00:51:25.157
So this is where you came in.

1308
00:51:25.273 --> 00:51:27.688
See. just like I said.
I'm the victim here.

1309
00:51:27.804 --> 00:51:29.605
I didn't do anything.
and they ruined my life

1310
00:51:29.721 --> 00:51:30.641
and took everything I had.

1311
00:51:30.755 --> 00:51:32.599
Hey. give it a rest
up there. will you?

1312
00:51:32.713 --> 00:51:34.898
What? I'm just telling
them what happened.

1313
00:51:35.014 --> 00:51:36.394
Who you kidding. pal?

1314
00:51:36.547 --> 00:51:38.543
They saw the whole thing.
they know what happened.

1315
00:51:38.657 --> 00:51:40.577
Well. yeah. but. But...

1316
00:51:40.692 --> 00:51:42.302
Just leave me alone.

1317
00:52:08.536 --> 00:52:11.985
The peasant at the diner!

1318
00:52:12.101 --> 00:52:14.556
He didn't pay his check.

1319
00:52:25.793 --> 00:52:27.675
He's the peasant
who I saw leaving the city

1320
00:52:27.789 --> 00:52:29.284
who disappeared
into the crowd

1321
00:52:29.400 --> 00:52:30.858
with Kuzco
on the back of his cart.

1322
00:52:30.934 --> 00:52:32.661
He must have taken him
back to his village.

1323
00:52:32.737 --> 00:52:34.387
so if we find the village.
we find him.

1324
00:52:34.463 --> 00:52:36.112
and if we find him.
we find Kuzco.

1325
00:52:36.190 --> 00:52:39.065
Oh. yeah.
it's all comin' together.

1326
00:52:39.409 --> 00:52:41.097
Yzma!

1327
00:52:41.213 --> 00:52:42.288
What?!

1328
00:52:42.364 --> 00:52:43.362
Aah!

1329
00:52:43.476 --> 00:52:46.735
This had
better be good!

1330
00:53:46.376 --> 00:53:47.489
Yeech.

1331
00:53:49.137 --> 00:53:51.248
So. there we were
standing on the cliff.

1332
00:53:51.400 --> 00:53:53.550
and the ground
started to rumble

1333
00:53:53.626 --> 00:53:55.543
And just as
it started to go.

1334
00:53:55.659 --> 00:53:57.231
he grabbed me
before I fell

1335
00:53:57.309 --> 00:53:58.880
Do you believe that?

1336
00:53:58.956 --> 00:54:00.298
You know. call me crazy

1337
00:54:00.376 --> 00:54:02.217
for following this guy
all the way out here.

1338
00:54:02.293 --> 00:54:03.942
but as much
as he tries to deny it.

1339
00:54:04.018 --> 00:54:05.478
I know
there's some good in him

1340
00:54:05.592 --> 00:54:08.315
Besides. I couldn't just
leave him out here all alone.

1341
00:54:08.391 --> 00:54:11.000
He's a lousy llama.

1342
00:54:11.077 --> 00:54:15.257
I mean.
a really lousy llama.

1343
00:54:26.074 --> 00:54:27.492
Hey. listen. Pacha.

1344
00:54:27.608 --> 00:54:30.445
you know. what I said to you
back at the diner.

1345
00:54:30.561 --> 00:54:33.438
that--that--
I--I didn't really...

1346
00:54:33.514 --> 00:54:36.237
So...you tired of
being a llama?

1347
00:54:37.311 --> 00:54:39.804
Ye-ee-ee-es!

1348
00:54:40.954 --> 00:54:42.719
Ok. we're just gonna
stop at the house

1349
00:54:42.873 --> 00:54:43.869
and get some supplies.

1350
00:54:43.983 --> 00:54:45.403
- Then we'll be on our way. right?
- Right.

1351
00:54:45.480 --> 00:54:48.434
Hey there. Pacha.
You just missed your relatives.

1352
00:54:48.510 --> 00:54:49.431
My relatives?

1353
00:54:49.507 --> 00:54:50.773
We just sent them
up to your house.

1354
00:54:50.889 --> 00:54:52.498
What did
they look like?

1355
00:54:52.614 --> 00:54:54.418
See. there was
this big guy

1356
00:54:54.532 --> 00:54:55.760
and this older woman
who was...

1357
00:54:55.835 --> 00:54:57.791
How would
you describe her?

1358
00:54:57.869 --> 00:54:59.289
Scary beyond all reason.

1359
00:54:59.364 --> 00:55:00.706
Yeah. that's it.

1360
00:55:01.358 --> 00:55:03.853
So. remind me again how
you're related to Pacha?

1361
00:55:03.929 --> 00:55:05.577
Why. I'm his
third cousin's brother's

1362
00:55:05.692 --> 00:55:08.838
wife's step-niece's
great-aunt. Heh heh.

1363
00:55:08.914 --> 00:55:11.983
Twice removed.

1364
00:55:12.099 --> 00:55:13.056
Uh-huh.

1365
00:55:13.172 --> 00:55:14.974
Isn't that right. Kronk?

1366
00:55:15.090 --> 00:55:17.315
99 monkeys
jumpin' on the bed

1367
00:55:17.391 --> 00:55:20.306
One fell off
and bumped his head

1368
00:55:20.420 --> 00:55:23.949
You know. I am so sorry that
you had to come all this way.

1369
00:55:24.103 --> 00:55:25.675
but as I said to you before.

1370
00:55:25.751 --> 00:55:28.436
you may recall.
Pacha is not here.

1371
00:55:28.552 --> 00:55:29.972
I'll be sure and tell him
you came by.

1372
00:55:30.086 --> 00:55:33.998
Oh. would you. please?
That would be just great.

1373
00:55:34.114 --> 00:55:36.414
Oops. Silly me.

1374
00:55:36.530 --> 00:55:38.715
No. no. Allow me.

1375
00:55:43.472 --> 00:55:44.853
She's hiding something.

1376
00:55:44.931 --> 00:55:46.271
When I give the word.
we search the house.

1377
00:55:46.347 --> 00:55:47.998
Ok. but I still have
94 monkeys to go.

1378
00:55:48.074 --> 00:55:49.532
Grr!

1379
00:55:49.646 --> 00:55:52.677
So. while we're
waiting for Paca--

1380
00:55:52.753 --> 00:55:54.288
Pacha.

1381
00:55:54.364 --> 00:55:55.706
Oh. yes.

1382
00:55:55.782 --> 00:55:58.123
Perhaps we can have a tour
of your lovely home.

1383
00:55:58.201 --> 00:56:00.039
You know. why don't
you just come back

1384
00:56:00.117 --> 00:56:01.536
when Pacha gets home?

1385
00:56:01.614 --> 00:56:04.530
I'm sure he'd love
to show you the...

1386
00:56:04.606 --> 00:56:06.447
Excuse me. won't you?

1387
00:56:06.523 --> 00:56:09.170
I think I left
something in the oven.

1388
00:56:09.246 --> 00:56:11.086
This is my variation
of double-dutch.

1389
00:56:11.164 --> 00:56:12.467
On the signal.
we switch places.

1390
00:56:12.545 --> 00:56:13.847
Kronk. it's time!

1391
00:56:13.925 --> 00:56:14.806
ok!

1392
00:56:14.884 --> 00:56:16.532
Ohh!

1393
00:56:16.610 --> 00:56:18.375
So. we have to get
back to the palace.

1394
00:56:18.489 --> 00:56:19.869
find the lab.
and change him back.

1395
00:56:19.985 --> 00:56:20.867
Hi there!

1396
00:56:20.943 --> 00:56:21.827
Aah!

1397
00:56:21.903 --> 00:56:24.242
- That was him.
- Whoops.

1398
00:56:26.007 --> 00:56:27.081
You know what?

1399
00:56:27.195 --> 00:56:29.228
I don't believe you're
really my great-aunt.

1400
00:56:29.344 --> 00:56:31.452
You're more like
my great-great-great...

1401
00:56:31.568 --> 00:56:33.139
Go. I'll stall them
long enough

1402
00:56:33.217 --> 00:56:34.177
for you two to get
a head start.

1403
00:56:34.331 --> 00:56:35.634
Thanks. honey.

1404
00:56:35.748 --> 00:56:37.552
You have a lovely wife.

1405
00:56:37.666 --> 00:56:38.740
They're both very pretty.

1406
00:56:38.818 --> 00:56:39.929
Great-great-
great...

1407
00:56:40.045 --> 00:56:42.422
Grr! All right!

1408
00:56:42.536 --> 00:56:44.224
Are you through?

1409
00:56:44.302 --> 00:56:45.182
...great-great-aunt.

1410
00:56:45.260 --> 00:56:46.181
So. where were we?

1411
00:56:46.295 --> 00:56:47.601
Listen. sister. we're
not leaving until--

1412
00:56:47.715 --> 00:56:49.480
I show you the house.
Of course.

1413
00:56:49.556 --> 00:56:52.817
Was it a good idea to leave
your family with those two?

1414
00:56:52.893 --> 00:56:55.463
Oh. don't worry.
They can handle themselves.

1415
00:56:55.577 --> 00:56:57.380
What do you mean.
the door is stuck?

1416
00:56:57.494 --> 00:56:59.030
Try jiggling the handle.

1417
00:56:59.106 --> 00:57:00.717
There is no handle
in here.

1418
00:57:00.831 --> 00:57:02.942
There's not?
Are you sure?

1419
00:57:03.056 --> 00:57:04.860
All right. I've had
enough of this.

1420
00:57:04.936 --> 00:57:06.817
Tell us where
the talking llama is

1421
00:57:06.931 --> 00:57:08.349
and we'll burn your house
to the ground.

1422
00:57:08.425 --> 00:57:09.998
Uh.
don't you mean "or"?

1423
00:57:10.112 --> 00:57:12.376
Tell us where
the talking llama is

1424
00:57:12.452 --> 00:57:14.371
or we'll burn your house
to the ground.

1425
00:57:14.487 --> 00:57:15.829
Well. which is it?

1426
00:57:15.905 --> 00:57:18.090
That seems like
a pretty crucial conjunction.

1427
00:57:18.168 --> 00:57:20.277
That's it!
Kronk. break the door down!

1428
00:57:20.393 --> 00:57:22.195
Break it down?
Are you kidding me?

1429
00:57:22.309 --> 00:57:23.538
This is hand-carved
mahogany.

1430
00:57:23.614 --> 00:57:25.876
I don't care. you fool.
Get out of my way.

1431
00:57:25.992 --> 00:57:27.219
I'll break it down myself.

1432
00:57:27.297 --> 00:57:28.563
A-one

1433
00:57:28.639 --> 00:57:29.943
Ok. kids.
you know what to do.

1434
00:57:30.978 --> 00:57:32.206
Right. Mom!

1435
00:57:32.360 --> 00:57:33.318
3!

1436
00:57:34.505 --> 00:57:35.811
Aah!

1437
00:57:44.211 --> 00:57:46.818
Ok. children.
on your mark.

1438
00:57:46.934 --> 00:57:48.967
get set. go!

1439
00:57:50.539 --> 00:57:53.146
Ow! Ow! Stop it.
you little brats! Huh?

1440
00:57:54.451 --> 00:57:55.523
Ow!

1441
00:57:55.601 --> 00:57:59.130
Oh. there they go. Kronk!
They're getting away!

1442
00:57:59.246 --> 00:58:02.275
Ha ha ha! Well.
I had a great time.

1443
00:58:02.351 --> 00:58:04.193
Let's not wait until
the next family reunion

1444
00:58:04.271 --> 00:58:05.420
to get together.

1445
00:58:05.496 --> 00:58:06.532
Kronk!

1446
00:58:06.610 --> 00:58:09.025
I. uh. I gotta run.

1447
00:59:14.420 --> 00:59:16.643
Ok. why does she even
have that lever?

1448
00:59:19.789 --> 00:59:21.132
Please remain seated

1449
00:59:21.248 --> 00:59:23.048
and keep your arms and legs
in at all times

1450
00:59:24.123 --> 00:59:25.579
Aah!

1451
00:59:27.077 --> 00:59:28.034
Huh?

1452
00:59:29.990 --> 00:59:31.525
What does it look like?

1453
00:59:31.641 --> 00:59:32.943
I don't know.
Just keep looking.

1454
00:59:33.021 --> 00:59:34.248
Over here!

1455
00:59:34.364 --> 00:59:38.197
It has to be one of these.
Lions. tigers. bears...

1456
00:59:38.275 --> 00:59:40.039
Oh. my

1457
00:59:40.155 --> 00:59:42.570
Looking for this?

1458
00:59:44.260 --> 00:59:45.601
No! It can't be!

1459
00:59:45.715 --> 00:59:47.518
How did you get
back here before us?

1460
00:59:47.597 --> 00:59:50.971
Uh...how did we. Kronk?

1461
00:59:51.047 --> 00:59:52.389
Well. you got me.

1462
00:59:52.467 --> 00:59:54.231
By all accounts.
it doesn't make sense.

1463
00:59:54.346 --> 00:59:56.418
Oh. well.
back to business.

1464
00:59:56.532 --> 00:59:57.875
Ok. I admit it.

1465
00:59:57.951 --> 00:59:59.945
Maybe I wasn't as nice
as I should have been.

1466
01:00:00.061 --> 01:00:02.670
but. Yzma. do you
really want to kill me?

1467
01:00:02.746 --> 01:00:06.083
Just think of it
as you're being let go.

1468
01:00:06.159 --> 01:00:08.077
that your life's going
in a different direction.

1469
01:00:08.152 --> 01:00:11.528
that your body's part of
a permanent outplacement.

1470
01:00:11.643 --> 01:00:13.447
Hey. that's kind of like
what he said to you

1471
01:00:13.561 --> 01:00:14.635
when you got fired.

1472
01:00:14.711 --> 01:00:17.512
I know. It's called
a cruel irony--

1473
01:00:17.588 --> 01:00:19.429
like my dependence
on you.

1474
01:00:19.505 --> 01:00:21.041
I can't believe
this is happening!

1475
01:00:21.117 --> 01:00:23.266
Then I bet you weren't
expecting this

1476
01:00:23.342 --> 01:00:24.684
- No!
- Aah!

1477
01:00:24.800 --> 01:00:26.181
Aha!

1478
01:00:26.257 --> 01:00:27.675
Oh. ok.

1479
01:00:27.751 --> 01:00:29.710
Ha ha!
Finish them off.

1480
01:00:31.626 --> 01:00:32.929
Hey. you're
not backing down now.

1481
01:00:33.083 --> 01:00:34.771
are you. big guy?

1482
01:00:35.844 --> 01:00:38.798
Uh. where's the other guy?

1483
01:00:38.876 --> 01:00:39.757
Yo!

1484
01:00:39.833 --> 01:00:42.251
Sorry I'm late.
So. what'd I miss?

1485
01:00:42.403 --> 01:00:43.862
Well. Yzma just
tossed me this knife

1486
01:00:43.976 --> 01:00:46.201
and asked me to.
you know. take them out.

1487
01:00:46.277 --> 01:00:49.000
Then this guy popped up
and we waited for you.

1488
01:00:49.114 --> 01:00:50.036
and quite honestly--

1489
01:00:50.150 --> 01:00:52.797
Kronk! Why did I think
you could do this?

1490
01:00:52.913 --> 01:00:54.217
This one simple thing.

1491
01:00:54.333 --> 01:00:55.675
It's like I'm talking
to a monkey.

1492
01:00:55.789 --> 01:00:56.786
Whoa now.

1493
01:00:56.902 --> 01:00:59.777
A really. really big
stupid monkey named Kronk!

1494
01:00:59.893 --> 01:01:00.775
Ouch.

1495
01:01:00.891 --> 01:01:02.309
And do you want
to know something else?

1496
01:01:02.385 --> 01:01:04.764
I've never liked
your spinach puffs.

1497
01:01:04.880 --> 01:01:06.260
Never!

1498
01:01:08.447 --> 01:01:10.134
That's it.
She's going down.

1499
01:01:10.210 --> 01:01:12.052
Now. now.
remember. guys.

1500
01:01:12.128 --> 01:01:14.737
From above. the wicked shall
receive their just reward.

1501
01:01:17.076 --> 01:01:18.956
That'll work.

1502
01:01:26.166 --> 01:01:28.007
Strange.
That usually works.

1503
01:01:28.123 --> 01:01:29.233
And so does this!

1504
01:01:29.311 --> 01:01:30.998
Ah. Should have
seen that coming.

1505
01:01:31.152 --> 01:01:32.570
Whoa!

1506
01:01:32.686 --> 01:01:34.373
Aah!

1507
01:01:34.449 --> 01:01:37.173
Give me that vial!

1508
01:01:37.250 --> 01:01:38.132
Oof!.

1509
01:01:38.208 --> 01:01:39.896
Ah! Ha ha!

1510
01:01:39.974 --> 01:01:41.353
Aah!

1511
01:01:44.996 --> 01:01:47.108
Oops. Clumsy me.

1512
01:01:48.489 --> 01:01:50.443
Which one? Which one?

1513
01:01:52.054 --> 01:01:55.623
Better hurry
I'm expecting company

1514
01:01:58.958 --> 01:02:02.411
Kill them!
They murdered the emperor!

1515
01:02:02.525 --> 01:02:05.094
No. wait! I'm the emperor!
It's me--Kuzco!

1516
01:02:05.210 --> 01:02:07.012
They're not
listening to me!

1517
01:02:07.126 --> 01:02:08.931
Just take 'em all!

1518
01:02:09.045 --> 01:02:10.771
- Yaah!
- Yaah!

1519
01:02:16.143 --> 01:02:17.023
Get them!

1520
01:02:17.101 --> 01:02:18.864
Hey. I've been
turned into a cow.

1521
01:02:18.978 --> 01:02:20.398
Can I go home?

1522
01:02:20.514 --> 01:02:22.085
You're excused.
Anyone else?

1523
01:02:22.201 --> 01:02:23.619
All: No. we're good.

1524
01:02:23.697 --> 01:02:24.771
Get them!

1525
01:02:24.885 --> 01:02:27.916
We've gotta change you back.
Try this one.

1526
01:02:30.409 --> 01:02:32.286
Uh. Pacha?
A little help!

1527
01:02:34.666 --> 01:02:36.201
Come on!
Come on!

1528
01:02:40.918 --> 01:02:43.259
Aah!

1529
01:02:43.335 --> 01:02:45.445
Oh. please be
something with wings.

1530
01:02:47.744 --> 01:02:50.393
Yeah! We're flyin'!

1531
01:02:50.507 --> 01:02:51.849
Uh-oh!

1532
01:02:57.257 --> 01:02:58.523
We're not getting anywhere
with you picking the vials.

1533
01:02:58.599 --> 01:02:59.748
I'm picking the next one!

1534
01:02:59.864 --> 01:03:01.246
Fine by me!

1535
01:03:01.322 --> 01:03:02.358
Give me that one!

1536
01:03:03.623 --> 01:03:05.233
Don't you say a word.

1537
01:03:05.351 --> 01:03:08.916
- Aah!
- Aah!

1538
01:03:10.643 --> 01:03:11.947
Quick!
Drain the canals!

1539
01:03:13.556 --> 01:03:14.746
Pacha: Open up!

1540
01:03:17.545 --> 01:03:19.809
Yay! I'm a llama again!

1541
01:03:19.885 --> 01:03:20.960
Wait...

1542
01:03:22.878 --> 01:03:24.181
- Aah!
- Aah!

1543
01:03:29.702 --> 01:03:31.737
There they go!
After them!

1544
01:03:31.891 --> 01:03:34.690
Come on. men!
Nobody lives forever! Charge!

1545
01:03:36.952 --> 01:03:38.911
Aah!

1546
01:03:38.987 --> 01:03:42.014
Grr!

1547
01:03:49.072 --> 01:03:52.065
Aah!

1548
01:03:52.179 --> 01:03:55.286
Ok. only 2 left. It's
gotta be one of these.

1549
01:03:59.775 --> 01:04:00.657
No!

1550
01:04:03.110 --> 01:04:07.637
Ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha!

1551
01:04:09.630 --> 01:04:10.512
Meow.

1552
01:04:10.590 --> 01:04:12.891
I'll take that.

1553
01:04:12.967 --> 01:04:15.307
This is the one. This'll
change you back to a human.

1554
01:04:15.422 --> 01:04:18.951
Ow! Hey. get her off!.

1555
01:04:19.065 --> 01:04:19.949
Whoa!

1556
01:04:20.025 --> 01:04:21.291
Get her off me!

1557
01:04:23.784 --> 01:04:25.356
Aah! Ow!

1558
01:04:29.153 --> 01:04:30.228
Drink the potion!

1559
01:04:30.342 --> 01:04:32.030
Ok. ok! Aah!

1560
01:04:32.106 --> 01:04:34.253
Where did it go?
Where is it?

1561
01:04:34.331 --> 01:04:36.708
Looking for this?

1562
01:04:36.786 --> 01:04:38.472
Is that my voice?

1563
01:04:38.550 --> 01:04:39.891
Is that my voice?

1564
01:04:39.967 --> 01:04:41.925
Oh. well.

1565
01:04:42.001 --> 01:04:43.114
No! Don't drop it!

1566
01:04:43.230 --> 01:04:45.570
I'm not going
to drop it. you fool!

1567
01:04:45.684 --> 01:04:47.793
I'm going to drink it!

1568
01:04:47.907 --> 01:04:50.670
And once I turn back
into my beautiful self.

1569
01:04:50.784 --> 01:04:52.588
I'm going to kill you!

1570
01:04:52.704 --> 01:04:56.422
Ha ha ha!

1571
01:05:01.561 --> 01:05:02.445
Aah!

1572
01:05:02.521 --> 01:05:03.786
Aah! Uh-oh.

1573
01:05:03.902 --> 01:05:05.206
Yzma: Aah!

1574
01:05:07.853 --> 01:05:08.733
Aah!

1575
01:05:10.039 --> 01:05:12.648
Aah! Aah!

1576
01:05:18.016 --> 01:05:19.588
Uhh! Whoa!

1577
01:05:20.739 --> 01:05:23.193
Uhh! Oh-oh-oh!

1578
01:05:24.268 --> 01:05:25.496
Kuzco!

1579
01:05:25.572 --> 01:05:26.952
Be right there!
Give me a minute!

1580
01:05:28.179 --> 01:05:29.445
Uhh! Uhh! Uhh!

1581
01:05:29.521 --> 01:05:30.942
Kuzco! Whoa!

1582
01:05:33.050 --> 01:05:34.010
Kuzco!

1583
01:05:34.969 --> 01:05:37.615
Aah!

1584
01:05:37.693 --> 01:05:39.034
Oh.

1585
01:05:40.876 --> 01:05:41.909
The vial!

1586
01:05:46.476 --> 01:05:50.387
Aah!

1587
01:05:50.503 --> 01:05:51.922
For the last time.

1588
01:05:51.998 --> 01:05:53.954
we did not order
a giant trampoline.

1589
01:05:54.068 --> 01:05:55.565
You know. pal. you
could have told me that

1590
01:05:55.641 --> 01:05:57.251
before I set it up.

1591
01:05:58.327 --> 01:06:00.896
Aah!

1592
01:06:01.012 --> 01:06:03.083
Aah! Uhh--

1593
01:06:03.159 --> 01:06:04.347
Huh? Ha ha ha.

1594
01:06:04.425 --> 01:06:06.764
Ha ha ha ha ha!

1595
01:06:06.840 --> 01:06:08.452
Hoo hoo hee hee
ha ha ha--

1596
01:06:11.902 --> 01:06:13.170
The vial!

1597
01:06:13.246 --> 01:06:15.242
You thinkin'
what I'm thinkin'?

1598
01:06:31.657 --> 01:06:33.306
Ah ha ha ha ha!

1599
01:06:33.382 --> 01:06:34.456
I win.

1600
01:06:34.570 --> 01:06:35.454
Whoa.

1601
01:06:37.525 --> 01:06:39.402
Got it!

1602
01:06:39.478 --> 01:06:42.280
What are the odds of that
trapdoor leading me out here?

1603
01:06:44.083 --> 01:06:45.617
Yeah!

1604
01:06:46.728 --> 01:06:47.612
Uhh.

1605
01:06:49.567 --> 01:06:52.021
Here. uh. let me
get this for you.

1606
01:06:54.324 --> 01:06:57.277
Well. see ya
on the other side.

1607
01:07:06.021 --> 01:07:07.440
Old man: Oh. now.
you--you

1608
01:07:07.516 --> 01:07:09.396
you stop being
so hard on yourself.

1609
01:07:09.474 --> 01:07:10.356
All is forgiven.

1610
01:07:10.432 --> 01:07:11.545
You're sure?

1611
01:07:11.621 --> 01:07:13.884
Oh. it's not the first time
I was tossed out a window.

1612
01:07:13.998 --> 01:07:15.458
and it won't be the last.

1613
01:07:15.572 --> 01:07:17.528
What can I say?
I'm a rebel.

1614
01:07:17.605 --> 01:07:18.793
Whoa-ho-ho. tiger.

1615
01:07:18.869 --> 01:07:21.016
Oh! Hey. I got to
use that arm later.

1616
01:07:21.094 --> 01:07:22.744
Ok. buddy. take care.

1617
01:07:22.822 --> 01:07:25.237
Ha ha.
Ah. he's a sweet guy.

1618
01:07:34.672 --> 01:07:37.088
So. you lied to me

1619
01:07:37.242 --> 01:07:39.005
I did?

1620
01:07:39.159 --> 01:07:41.192
Yeah. You said
when the sun

1621
01:07:41.306 --> 01:07:42.458
hits this ridge
just right.

1622
01:07:42.574 --> 01:07:43.954
these hills sing.

1623
01:07:44.030 --> 01:07:46.063
Well. pal. I was dragged
all over those hills.

1624
01:07:46.179 --> 01:07:49.360
and I did not hear
any singing.

1625
01:07:51.126 --> 01:07:52.047
So

1626
01:07:52.201 --> 01:07:53.619
I'll be building
my summer home

1627
01:07:53.733 --> 01:07:57.530
on a more magical hill.
Thank you.

1628
01:07:59.679 --> 01:08:02.364
Hmm. Couldn't pull the wool
over your eyes. huh?

1629
01:08:02.518 --> 01:08:04.166
No. no. I'm sharp.
I'm on it.

1630
01:08:04.242 --> 01:08:05.393
Looks like you
and your family

1631
01:08:05.509 --> 01:08:07.657
are stuck on that tuneless
hill top forever. pal.

1632
01:08:16.247 --> 01:08:18.587
You know. I'm pretty sure
I heard some singing

1633
01:08:18.663 --> 01:08:21.042
on the hill next to us.

1634
01:08:21.195 --> 01:08:22.500
In case you're interested.

1635
01:08:27.064 --> 01:08:28.597
Ha! Boom. baby!

1636
01:08:28.751 --> 01:08:30.744
Ha! Boom. baby!

1637
01:08:34.658 --> 01:08:36.038
You'd be the coolest dude

1638
01:08:36.115 --> 01:08:37.381
In the nation

1639
01:08:37.496 --> 01:08:39.182
Or the hippest cat
in creation

1640
01:08:39.297 --> 01:08:42.252
But if you ain't got friends.
then nothing's worth the fuss

1641
01:08:43.900 --> 01:08:45.779
A perfect world
will come to be

1642
01:08:45.856 --> 01:08:48.082
When everybody here
can see

1643
01:08:48.198 --> 01:08:50.306
That a perfect world
begins and ends

1644
01:08:50.421 --> 01:08:52.453
A perfect world
begins and ends

1645
01:08:52.569 --> 01:08:55.176
A perfect world
begins and ends with us.

1646
01:08:56.404 --> 01:08:58.091
"My acorn
is missing."

1647
01:08:58.168 --> 01:09:00.087
Squeak squeakin'
squeak squeakity.

1648
01:09:00.203 --> 01:09:01.659
"Did you eat
the acorn?"

1649
01:09:01.775 --> 01:09:03.769
Squeaker squeak
squeak squeakin'?

1650
01:09:03.884 --> 01:09:05.609
"You owe me
a new acorn."

1651
01:09:05.685 --> 01:09:07.872
Squeak squeak squeak
squeak squeaker--

1652
01:09:10.905 --> 01:09:11.979
Squeakin'.

1653
01:09:11.500 --> 01:09:12.094
I'm so proud of you guys.

